Author:  SWAINSON
Vol / Page:  91
Edition:
Quote:  The bed of the Kapanga, in which the gold was found, consists of rocks of quartz, trap, and a bluish granite containing iron pyrites... In the detritus on the sides of the mountains, and in the beds of the stream, quartz occurs in detached blocks of various sizes, mixed with fragments of slate, granite and trap; but regular dykes of quartz are not generally met with, although they are reported to exist.
